            <title>[LUCENE-3796] Disallow setBoost() on StringField, throw exception if boosts are set if norms are omitted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3796</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Occasionally users are confused why index-time boosts are not applied to their norms-omitted fields.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because we silently discard the boost: there is no reason for this!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The most absurd part: in 4.0 you can make a StringField and call setBoost and nothing complains... (more reasons to remove StringField totally in my opinion)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
